        "body": "For this and the next three lessons, recite a prayer you know by heart to open each\nclass period, such as the one suggested in Section 19. After you and a few of the children\nhave said opening devotions, you can present to them the prayer below, the final one they\nwill memorize in this grade.\n“O Thou kind Lord! I am a little child, exalt me by admitting me to the kingdom.\nI am earthly, make me heavenly; I am of the world below, let me belong to the\nrealm above; gloomy, suffer me to become radiant; material, make me spiritual,\nand grant that I may manifest Thine infinite bounties.\n“Thou art the Powerful, the All-Loving.” 123"
