        "key": "drama",
        "title": "Drawing and art",
        "body": "As with the other lessons in this set, you will need to select one or two activities for the\nchildren to carry out that will strengthen their artistic skills and help them think further about\nthe theme of the lesson. The activity could, for instance, build on the exercise they did during\nthe drama portion of the lesson, where they imagined some of the tasks that are part of certain\nprofessions. In that case, you could help them extend the skills they developed in creating forms\nin order to make objects that are used in those professions, for example, a doctor’s bag, a judge’s\ngavel, an artist’s paint palette, a gardener’s rake, and so on."
